title: #LetThemEatPie
description: Diana Prince is a distant underdog when she enters a pie-eating contest against Barry Allen and Doris Zeul.

title: #WorkingStiff
description: After Babs hooks Karen up with a job at the Burrito Bucket the two heroes encounter a new villain, the scourge of the fast-food underworld, the Condiment King!

title: #RageCat
description: Jessica Cruz is convinced she can find the purr-fect forever home for Dexter, a cat who has been deemed unadoptable because he's basically the worst cat in the world. Her overbearing persistence in trying to get him adopted leads Dexter to become Dex-Starr, an evil Red Lantern supervillain! Can Jess still find the good in a fuzzy little nemesis who is trying to kill her?

title: #FreshPrincessOfRenFaire Part 2
description: A fun day at the Renaissance Faire takes a dark turn when our heroes clash with a princess-eating dragon.

title: #FreshPrincessOfRenFaire Part 1
description: A fun day at the Renaissance Faire takes a dark turn when our heroes clash with a princess-eating dragon.

title: #HashtagFrownyFace
description: Batgirl finds herself in trouble with Poison Ivy when her reinforcement, Diana Prince, can't understand her text messages.

title: #StressTest
description: Barbara Gordon gets a message that Batgirl is needed...while she's in the middle of a very important test.

title: Power Outage
description: It's Wonder Woman's first day of Flyer's Ed and her chance to prove to Red Tornado, the instructor, what a great flyer she is. But her lap through the aerial obstacle course is fraught with disaster when Cheetah takes control of Wonder Woman's flight safety belt.

title: Need for Speed
description: The Flash is running wild in Metropolis! Lena Luthor has strapped a confusion inducing Blue Kryptomite to his back and now he's running so fast that he's shaking the foundations of Metropolis. It's up to the girls at Super Hero High; Batgirl, Wonder Woman, Supergirl and Bumblebee, to stop The Flash in his tracks and save Metropolis!

title: Hero of the Month: Supergirl
description: Supergirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: #HappyBirthdayZee
description: Zatanna makes a birthday wish that forces her to confront the dark side of her magic.

title: #MisgivingTree
description: Jessica Cruz and Pam Isley bond over protecting an ancient tree from being cut down. Neither of them realizes who the other's alter ego is, or the lengths to which they'll go to protect what's important.

title: Spring Prison Break
description: Frost reads her "How I Spent Spring Break" essay and we flashback to the tale of how Katana and Frost formed the first "Task Force X" to stop Lashina from breaking the Female Furies out of Belle Reve. During the battle between the SHH Heroes and the Furies, Barda redeems herself and joins the side of the good guys.

title: Stealth 101 Part 2
description: Batgirl and Ivy learn to appreciate each other's style as they fight Killer Moth.

title: #AllAboutZee
description: Zee Zatara is flattered when she meets an overeager admirer named Casey Krinsky, but soon realizes that "her biggest fan" wants much more than just an autograph.

title: #BreakingNews
description: Lois Lane's attempt to get an internship at the Daily Planet leads to her trying to unmask the Super Hero Girls, which forces the girls to a battle of wits with their greatest nemesis yet.

title: #AmBatgirl Part 1
description: Batgirl finally has the chance to live out her life's dream and be the sidekick to her hero and inspiration - the Batman!

title: Dude, Where's My Invisible Jet?
description: Wonder Woman loses her invisible jet.

title: #WasabiWar
description: Zee Zatara's attempt to broaden Kara Danvers's horizons by taking her for a sushi dinner ends in disaster.

title: #WhySoBlue
description: Supergirl must rein in a reckless new hero, the Blue Beetle.

title: Hero of the Month: Hawkgirl
description: Hawkgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: #Powerless
description: Supergirl loses her powers and, with the help of BumbleBee, must rely on her street smarts to save Garth from vengeful Toyman.

title: #TacoTuesday
description: Karen Beecher gets the last taco on Taco Tuesday, but Doris Zeul will do everything in her power to make sure she doesn't keep it.

title: #AllyCat Part 2
description: When Zee Zatara realizes Lex Luthor has unearthed a magical book with the power to tell the future, the girls reluctantly enlist Catwoman to help them steal it from him before he understands what he has, but it may already be too late.

title: #LostAndFound
description: Harley Quinn wreaks havoc all over Metropolis when she finds Wonder Woman's missing Lasso of Truth.

title: #WarriorAndTheJester
description: After accidentally destroying one of Babs' beloved, one-of-a-kind Batman keepsakes, Diana enlists the help of Harleen Quinzel in order to find a replacement in Gotham City.

title: Surprise
description: Harley enlists the help of Katana and Bumblebee in hiding a surprise birthday present for Batgirl in her dorm room. But when they sneak into Batgirl's dorm, they are accosted by Batgirl's booby traps.

title: The Blunder Games
description: As part of the Advanced Survival Skills class, Batgirl is dropped off in a remote island and must make it to the designated meeting spot before sunset. But when her equipment malfunctions, Batgirl must rely on a different set of super skills.

title: License to Fly
description: Batgirl builds her Batjet. But before she can fly, she must pass the Flyer's Exam.

title: Showdown
description: The Furies are back and this time they've stolen a very important document from Principal Waller that could have dire ramifications for Superhero High and the World! It's up to Wonder Woman and Katana to take down the Furies and save the day!

title: Designing Disaster
description: Wonder Woman finishes her super suit for Crazy Quilt's class and it's time to try it out. But the suit is a mish-mash of super hero tropes and isn't practical for saving the day. Her attempts to respond to a Save the Day drill end in disaster as her suit trips her up.

title: Dog Day After School
description: A Krytptonian is loose in Metropolis! After following the wake of school destruction, Supergirl is reunited with Krypto the Super Dog.

title: #SoulSisters Part 1
description: The girls must track down Katana, a mysterious warrior who's stealing the souls of Metropolis's villains. Meanwhile, Diana's new friend Tatsu is a perfect match for her in every way, but may have a connection to Katana.

title: #GothamCon
description: A fun day for Barbara Gordon and her bestie Harleen Quinzel (at Gotham City's annual geekfest, the Annual Convention of Gotham City Enthusiats!) is turned on its head when, out of nowhere, the villainous Harley Quinn shows up to wreak havoc! Lucky for everyone, Batgirl just happens to be in the area...

title: #SuperSleeper
description: When Kara Danvers sleep-flies out of the Gordon house, it's up to Barbara Gordon to bring her back down to Earth before her secret identity is exposed.

title: #LivingTheNightmare
description: When Zee's friends are held captive in their nightmares by a dream demon, she'll have to confront her own hidden insecurities, or risk the Super Hero Girls being trapped in a prison of their own fears forever.

title: #FightAtTheMuseum
description: Supergirl always relies on her strength, but she'll need more than brawn to stop brainy Catwoman from stealing valuable gems from the local science museum.

title: #BigScreenBully
description: Karen Beecher is psyched to see the next installment in her favorite movie franchise until Doris Zeul shows up and tries to ruin the experience.

title: Get to Know You: Carter Hall - Hawkman
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Carter Hall, AKA Hawkman. He's the strong, silent type, and also the perfect partner for Bumblebee.

title: Get to Know You: Carter Hall - Hawkman
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Carter Hall, AKA Hawkman. He's the strong, silent type, and also the perfect partner for Bumblebee.

title: #SweetJustice Part 4
description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

title: Hero of the Month: Lady Shiva
description: Lady Shiva is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Lego DC Super Hero Girls: Brain Drain
description: Missing memories provide an intriguing mystery for everyone's favorite young female heroes in this all-new animated film.  When Supergirl, Wonder Woman, Batgirl, Harley Quinn, Bumblebee, Poison Ivy and Katana suddenly realize they cannot remember a single moment from their Monday at Super Hero High, the young Super Heroes spring into sleuthing action! Suspecting foul-play, they band together to retrace their steps and uncover the mystery of who exactly stole their memories - and, what nefarious plan might be afoot?

title: Franken-Ivy
description: Ivy creates a new plant pet which grows out-of-control and attacks Metropolis.

title: #HardRock
description: Diana Prince's first experience at the Lazarus Pit goes horribly wrong when she mistakes a mosh pit for an actual brawl.

title: #TheMinus
description: Diana receives her first ever A minus and becomes convinced that she needs to work harder, however, in order to do so, she resorts to rather drastic measures.

title: For Art's Sake
description: It's the SHH Student Art Fundraiser and the Double Dare Twins have stolen a masterpiece from the show! It's up to Katana and Supergirl to stop them and recover the painting. But when Supergirl is knocked out by kryptonite and Katana's sword is stolen, Katana must improvise and use her art supplies to defeat the Double Dare Twins.

title: #TheGoodTheBadAndTheBizarre
description: Everything is going well for Kara Danvers, both as a teen and a superhero, until she starts taking the blame for things she didn't do, and the emergence of a new supervillain threatens to destroy Supergirl's hard-earned reputation.

title: #RemoteUncontrolled
description: When they can't agree on a show to watch, Harleen Quinzel and Pam Isley end up in a super battle over the remote.

title: #Abracadabrapalooza
description: In an attempt to make Karen feel better about a pimple, Zee recounts her embarrassing transition into magichood, and the rift it created between her and her father.

title: #BeastsInShow
description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 2
description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

title: #ComicGone
description: Barbara Gordon and Harleen Quinzel both covet the same rare comic book, but don't want to let it come between them. Batgirl and Harley Quinn, on the other hand.

title: #SpeedyDelivery
description: he Flash encounters a variety of obstacles when he must deliver a dessert across town in under ten minutes.

title: Get to Know You: Oliver Queen - Green Arrow
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Oliver Queen, AKA Green Arrow. A master thespian who's also a master archer, with as much passion for the spotlight as Zatanna.

title: Get to Know You: Oliver Queen - Green Arrow
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Oliver Queen, AKA Green Arrow. A master thespian who's also a master archer, with as much passion for the spotlight as Zatanna.

title: Stealth 101 Part 1
description: Batgirl and Ivy are partnered for Crazy Quilt's stealth suit design project.

title: Jetsetters
description: Wonder Woman is teaching Frost how to fly the Invisible Jet when Killer Moth detects them and begins to attack. Frost takes the ejector Turbo Seat to fight back. However, the jet is damaged by Killer Moth's ship, and the jet begins to plummet. The ship goes into emergency lockdown and Wonder Woman is trapped. She manages to lift the jet from the inside and crash into the bay instead of the city. Frost makes a giant ice cube that allows the jet to float and freezes Killer Moth's plane. With Killer Moth defeated, Supergirl melts the ice around Wonder Woman's jet and Batgirl restores functionality to the jet's tech. Wonder Woman emerges unscathed.

title: Techless Tuesday
description: Mrs. Clayface steals all of Batgirl's gadgets in an effort to break her husband out of Arkham.

title: #SweetJustice Part 3
description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

title: Wildside Part 2
description: With Lion-Mane subdued, Batgirl, Starfire, and Beast Boy must find all the escaped zoo animals and return them to the zoo. With the help of zoo volunteer, Mari McCabe (Vixen), they return the animals to their proper place at the zoo.

title: Batgirl
description: Get to know the new Super Hero Girl - Batgirl/Barbara Gordon - starring in the new DC Super Hero Girls series on Cartoon Network!

title: New Beginnings
description: Wonder Woman shows Supergirl around Super Hero High.

title: Crazy Quiltin
description: Wonder Woman is introduced to an important rite-of-passage for all new students at the school: creating your own iconic super hero suit. But super suit design is not Wonder Woman's forte. She brings in Katana, Bumblebee, and Harley to help her in this important task, but the results leave something to be desired.

title: All About Super Hero High
description: Wonder Woman arrives at Super Hero High. Waller introduces Bumblebee as the Ambassador to New Students. Bumblebee gives Wonder Woman the tour of Super Hero High and introduces her to some of the main Supers.

title: Hero of the Month: Batgirl
description: Batgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Hero of the Month: Bumblebee
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Bumblebee. Waller shows a video montage of Bumblebee's exploits including saving her friends plus little comedic beats where Bumblebee changing size causes her to split a seam in her costume.

title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 2
description: The supers must save Metropoils from the army of Kryptomites.

title: Hero of the Month: Star Sapphire
description: Star Sapphire is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: #HamsterConQueso
description: When Hammy the hamster gets loose in Burrito Bucket, it's up to Barbara Gordon to catch him before the health inspector does.

title: #Vegecide
description: Jessica Cruz does battle with her own smoothie when Poison Ivy wreaks havoc on a vegan restaurant.

title: Fresh Ares Part 3
description: With Catwoman's help, the supers return the amulet to Ares and save the day.

title: Wonder Woman
description: Get to know the new Super Hero Girl - Wonder Woman/Diana Prince - starring in the new DC Super Hero Girls series on Cartoon Network!

title: Welcome to Super Hero High
description: The school's official greeting video hosted by Principal Waller. Principal Waller introduces the school and curriculum to potential new students.

title: Get to Know You: Hal Jordon - Green Lantern
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Hal Jordan, the Big Man on Campus at Metropolis High. And as a Green Lantern like Jessica Cruz, he's the guy you want by your side.

title: Get to Know You: Hal Jordon - Green Lantern
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Hal Jordan, the Big Man on Campus at Metropolis High. And as a Green Lantern like Jessica Cruz, he's the guy you want by your side.

title: Batgirl vs. Supergirl
description: Batgirl and Supergirl face off in a quest for the last piece of superfood cake.

title: Quintessential Harley
description: When Harley's web videos go viral, she deals with the unexpected consequences of fame.

title: #MeetTheCheetah
description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

title: Fight Flub
description: Katana and Big Barda try to prove their own fighting style is the best when the Double Dare Twins attack.

title: Around Metropolis in 80 Seconds
description: Wonder Woman and Supergirl are facing off to see who's fastest, but when they keep tying, they decide to race sans superpowers. Harley hates to be left out and joins the race. As Wonder Woman and Supergirl zoom around Metropolis, they spot a bank robbery in progress and compete to see who can catch the criminals first. While they're distracted, Harley wins the race.

title: #BackInAFlash
description: After an embarrassing incident ruins Barbara Gordon's reputation, rather than owning it and moving on, she decides it's easier to harness The Flash's newly discovered ability to travel back in time and alter the delicate fabric of the space-time continuum.

title: New Perry-Spective
description: Batgirl, Big Barda, and Lady Shiva set off in the Mobile HQ to wrangle Perry the Parademon. Perry playfully destroys various bits of Metropolis as the supers chase him. The supers manage to catch him and wait in anticipation, thinking Granny Goodness is behind this. However, it seems Perry has been abandoned by his previous owner, and just wants to play. Big Barda decides to keep Perry as her pet.

title: Doubles Trouble
description: Katana chooses Supergirl as her tennis doubles partner, but Supergirl's powers are too much for the game.

title: #FaultyPowers
description: Batgirl's malfunctioning gadgets cause her to lose confidence in her abilities.

title: Ring of Mire
description: Star Sapphire loses her violet lantern ring down the drain and must venture into the sewers. Ew ew ew!

title: #AngerManagement
description: When Jess coerces Kara into addressing her anger management issues, Supergirl's superhero abilities become seriously compromised!

title: #AdventuresInBunnysitting
description: Zee asks Kara to look after her two magical bunnies, which quickly start to multiply, wreaking havoc all across Metropolis.

title: #ShockItToMe
description: Leslie Willis, the meanest girl in school, becomes a social media sensation by posting mean-spirited videos on her MetropoVids channel, causing Wonder Woman to question the moral integrity of the people who live in the World of Man.

title: #DinnerForFive
description: Barbara Gordon finds herself in a tight spot when an awkward dinner with a new friend's father turns into something so much more.

title: Day of Fun-Ship
description: Starfire and Blackfire must protect the zoo from King Shark and realize they have more in common than they thought.

title: DC Super Hero Girls: Super Hero High
description: Supergirl arrives at Super Hero High and struggles to learn to control her new powers. Meanwhile, the Junior Detective Club investigates a mysterious rash of security breaches centered around the teleportation Boom Tubes.

title: #MotherKnowsBest
description: Hippolyta visits town and Diana is desperate to win her approval. But when Hippolyta unexpectedly takes a shine to Kara, Diana must curb her envy before they all get hurt.

title: #MultipliciZee
description: Zee magically duplicates herself so she can shirk work and watch TV. Things get out of hand when her copies start to make copies of themselves!

title: #EqualTights
description: Green Lantern (Hal) tries to impress his hero, Superman, with his heroing prowess.

title: Body Electric
description: Giganta causes an electric blackout and Batgirl enlists the help of Thunder and Lightning,

title: Bodybuilding
description: Batgirl, Bumblebee and Cyborg have teamed up for the Creative Heroic Engineering Project at Superhero High. The only problem is they can't agree on anything! When Lena Luthor attacks with her new Rainbow Kryptomites our heroes will have to learn to work together to defeat her.

title: Trading Places
description: Lena Luthor has created a power nullifying device and she is threatening to use it on Superhero High! Now, Batgirl and Supergirl will have to trade places to infiltrate Lena's lab and put the power nullifying device out of commission for good.

title: Seeing Red
description: A red Kryptomite, loose at Super Hero High, brings out everyone's mean side.

title: #SuperWho?
description: Overwhelmed by the amount of Superman coverage in Metropolis, Supergirl decides to get out there and really show the city what she can do. But when Superman inadvertently puts everyone in harm's way, Supergirl has to decide whether to do what's good for the people or what's good for her ego.

title: Supergirl
description: Get to know the new Super Hero Girl - Supergirl/Kara Danvers - starring in the new DC Super Hero Girls series on Cartoon Network!

title: #AcceptNoSubstitute
description: Feeling smothered, Babs urges her retired dad, Commissioner Gordon, to get a hobby, but her advice backfires when the Commissioner becomes a substitute teacher at her school!

title: Weaponomics
description: It's demonstration day in Lucius Fox's Weaponomics class. Catwoman wields her whip. Hawkgirl swings her mace. But when Wonder Woman demonstrates her lasso, a sneaky maneuver from Cheetah causes her to lasso Mr. Fox, who spills his secrets in the lasso's grip. The incident leads to Wonder Woman getting detention!

title: #CrashCourse
description: When a high-speed chase breaks out during her driver's test, Diana Prince's desire to fight evil clashes with her desire to undergo a World of Man teenage rite of passage, getting her license.

title: #TheGreenRoom
description: When Jessica is faced with a Green Lantern Corps disciplinary hearing, Hal appoints himself to be her Peer Advocate.

title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

title: The Cheetah Who Cried Wolf
description: Cheetah attempts to win Hero of the Month through various Save the Day situations.

title: #SoulSisters Part 2
description: The girls must track down Katana, a mysterious warrior who's stealing the souls of Metropolis's villains. Meanwhile, Diana's new friend Tatsu is a perfect match for her in every way, but may have a connection to Katana.

title: #ScrambledEggs
description: It's egg-xactly what you think: the home economics "Egg-Baby" assignment, where students are paired up and given an egg to "care for" over a weekend. But when tragedy befalls egg after egg, what should be an easy assignment escalates into a madcap romp with super-high stakes!

title: #WorldsFinest
description: When PR whiz Max Lord tells Batgirl and Supergirl he can improve their image by doing publicity stunts, the two friends forget what being a hero is really about.

title: #KaraCare
description: After absorbing too much kryptonite during an epic battle, Supergirl takes advantage of Wonder Woman's nurturing nature.

title: #DramaQueen
description: Oliver Queen must face off against his greatest rival yet, Mortimer Drake, while Green Arrow also finds himself up against a new foe, The Cavalier.

title: #DyeHarder
description: Zee Zatara's hairstylist goes to extreme lengths to give Kara Danvers's super-hair a cut.

title: Fresh Ares Part 1
description: A peaced out Ares comes to Metropolis to see Wonder Woman, but his peaceful outlook is ruined when Catwoman steals the Amulet of Harmonia.

title: #FantasticBeastsAndHowToMindThem
description: Diana Prince receives a care package from home, and her pet-raising skills are soon put to the test when a mysterious egg hatches into a baby griffin.

title: #SweetJustice Part 2
description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

title: The Odd Couple
description: Harley and Lady Shiva are paired for a stake out assignment and must capture a villainous named Cheshire.

title: #Batcatcher
description: Batgirl faces one of her greatest adversaries yet when a stray bat gets into her bedroom.

title: #BatAndSwitch
description: Zee Zatara's attempts to help Barbara Gordon see eye to eye with her father backfire when her magic spell doesn't work as planned.

title: Hero of the Month: Frost
description: Frost is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: #AllyCat Part 1
description: When Zee Zatara realizes Lex Luthor has unearthed a magical book with the power to tell the future, the girls reluctantly enlist Catwoman to help them steal it from him before he understands what he has, but it may already be too late.

title: #FromBatToWorse
description: Having just moved to the boring Metropolis suburbs, Batgirl is thrilled when she intercepts a call from Batman asking for help. But before she can stop a visiting Gotham villain, she'll have to sneak past her dad, Police Commissioner Gordon.

title: Riddle of the Heart
description: The Riddler stages a series of crimes in order to lure Batgirl to the rose garden where he asks her to the dance.

title: A Fury Scorned
description: Lashina breaks into Belle Reve and poisons Commissioner Gordon. Batgirl and Hawkgirl must find the antidote before it's too late.

title: #StreetStyle
description: Kara Danvers sets out for picture day at school in a nice dress but the heroing she must do along the way leaves her looking more punk than pretty.

title: #PowerSurge
description: When Supergirl is presumed dead after a battle with Livewire, Kara Danvers decides to reinvent herself with a new look, a new personality, and a new name, Power Girl.

title: Gorilla Warfare
description: The supers must save Gorilla Grodd when his former army comes to "rescue" him from SHH.

title: #NightmareInGotham
description: Babs and Harleen bring the Girls to Gotham City to celebrate Halloween! However, the fun is put on hold when the SuperHero Girls run into Gotham's most notorious SuperVillain.

title: #HateTriangle
description: When Hal's ex-girlfriend shows up at the Metropolis High homecoming game and goes love-ballistic as the villain Star Sapphire, Jessica begins to second-guess her own nonviolent tactics.

title: #Retreat!
description: Jessica Cruz and some super friends go on an overnight camping trip without their powers and are attacked by Poison Ivy and a horde of Plant Zombies!

title: Cold Blooded
description: Frost catches a cold and each sneeze and sniffle causes her to freeze everything around her.

title: #Frenemies Part 2
description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

title: It's a Superful Life
description: The girls want to make this an extra special holiday by brightening the lives of Metropolis citizens.

title: Roomies Return: Frost's Bite
description: When Frost can't get her warmth from any of her normal sources, her grumpiness causes icy havoc around the school.

title: #ItsComplicated
description: When Hal Jordan sees Carol Ferris with a new boyfriend, his ego can't handle the rejection, resulting in the most absurd Lantern battle ever.

title: Fall into Super Hero High
description: Harley Quinn reveals she made a tribute video for her friends, which they learn is a montage of them screwing up while using their powers. Their embarrassment is heightened when they learn Harley has accidentally uploaded the video and it's gone viral! Seeing the absurdity and laughing at herself, Wonder Woman breaks the girls' stunned, mortified silence. The laugh catches on. Because of Wonder Woman's leadership, all the girls who were initially embarrassed are able to laugh at themselves.

title: Hero of the Month: Katana
description: Katana is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Clubbing
description: Principal Waller tells Poison Ivy that she needs to join a club in order to fulfill her extracurricular requirements. However, clubs are not introverted Ivy's idea of fun. Hawkgirl and Bumblebee invite Ivy to join the Junior Detective Society. Miss Martian and Starfire give Ivy the pitch for the Model United Planets. Katana and Beast Boy want her for Band Club. But then, the glimmering test tubes of Science Club catch Ivy's eye. Ivy adds her name to the sign-up sheet manned by Frost and Flash. Later, during the first Science Club meeting, Ivy shows off her modified plants, which creates chaos for Star Sapphire. Ivy grins. Clubs are fun!

title: #AmBatgirl Part 2
description: Batgirl finally has the chance to live out her life's dream and be the sidekick to her hero and inspiration - the Batman!

title: #DoubleDanvers
description: When Kara realizes that she needs to be in two places on the same night, a dinner with an important investor in her parents' startup and a concert for her favorite band, the Malevolent Maniaxe at the Lazarus Pit, she calls for reinforcements in the form of Bizarro Kara!

title: #TheAquamanCometh
description: For months, Garth's been sending Aquaman letters that greatly exaggerate his accomplishments in Metropolis, so when the King of Atlantis comes for a surprise visit, Garth begs the Super Hero Girls to help cover for his little white lies.

title: #Frenemies Part 1
description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

title: #SilverScream
description: Kara Danvers is excited to see a new horror movie, but must contend with a theater full of rude patrons.

title: #CruzControl
description: Working toward her dream of making her school a better place, Jessica runs for class president. However, when her opponent, the corrupt Oswald Cobblepot, pulls ahead in the race using less-than-honest means, Jessica finds herself compromising the integrity of her honest campaign to beat him!

title: Zatanna
description: Get to know the new Super Hero Girl - Zatanna/Zee Zatara - starring in the new DC Super Hero Girls series on Cartoon Network!

title: #SofaSoGood
description: When Babs finds a ratty old sofa that she thinks will be perfect for the hideout, she recruits Karen to help her get it there.

title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 1
description: Lena Luthor uses kryptonite remnants from Supergirl's ship to create living Kryptomites.

title: #PictureDaze
description: When Carol Ferris sees Jessica Cruz give Hal Jordan some last minute sprucing up for picture day, she takes it as flirting, triggering a battle between Star Sapphire and Green Lantern.

title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 1
description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

title: Get to Know You: Garth - Aqualad
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Garth, AKA Aqualad. He may not be very tall, but he's huge on confidence. Being Master of the Oceans will do that for you.

title: Get to Know You: Garth - Aqualad
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Garth, AKA Aqualad. He may not be very tall, but he's huge on confidence. Being Master of the Oceans will do that for you.

title: Wonder Waitress
description: Wonder Woman is used to saving the world from dire threats a couple of times a week but this time she'll face her greatest challenge yet: Waitressing. When Steve Trevor's waitress quits her job mid shift at Capes and Cowls Café it's up to Wonder Woman to step in and save the day!

title: #EnterNightSting
description: Karen is given a mission to prevent the apocalypse by DeathSting, a super-cool future version of herself.

title: #Beeline

description: Cyborg and Starfire are both anointed Hero of the Month.

description: Beast Boy is anointed Hero of the Month.

description: Meek little Karen Beecher is intimidated by big broody Carter Hall - both as a hero and a teen - until she discovers Hawkman's tragically romantic destiny and vows to use her vast knowledge of cheesy teen movies to help him reunite with his beloved.

description: Super Hero High is facing off against Korugar Academy in the Intergalactic Games, but Lena Luthor takes advantage of the gathering of supers to enact her villainous plan.

title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 1
description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

title: Saving the Day
description: It's time for Wonder Woman to reveal her new super suit for Crazy Quilt's final grade. Bumblebee, Harley and Ivy watch from the sidelines in support of their friend. Wonder Woman steps onto the catwalk and reveals her new outfit. But before Crazy Quilt announces Wonder Woman's grade, the Save the Day alarm buzzes! Wearing her new costume, Wonder Woman leads Bumble Bee, Harley, and Ivy on a mission to save the day! They must save Mr. Fox who's stuck on top of the Amethyst! The girls save their teacher, but in the process, Wonder Woman discovers that Cheetah was behind this malicious deed. In the grip of Wonder Woman's lasso, Cheetah confesses all her crimes.

title: #SweetJustice Part 1
description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

title: Fresh Ares Part 2
description: As Ares reigns destruction on Metropolis, the supers must recover the amulet.

title: #SuperWonderBatBeeZeeLanterMobile
description: The Super Hero Girls decide to go in together to buy their first car, but quickly learn that splitting an automobile six ways may prove to be their deadliest foe yet!

title: #PrizeFighter
description: Kara Danvers's competitive nature kicks into high gear when she can't get a single prize at the games on the pier, while Barbara Gordon seems to win with ease.

title: #OneEnchantedEvening
description: Zee worries that Zatara is lonely and volunteers to play matchmaker for her dad.  But when her meddlesome match-matching accidentally sets her dad up with an old enemy, Zee must find a way to fix the mess she made!

title: The Ultimate Accessory
description: Bumblebee must design an accessory for her Weaponomics class. But instead of designing for herself, she finds more inspiration in her friends.

description: Mad Harriet has stolen Batgirl's Batjet and she's threatening Superhero High with it. Batgirl, Wonder Woman, Supergirl and Harley Quinn have to stop her. But as dangerous as Mad Harriet being on the loose is will Harley Quinn's help be even worse?

When a bank robbery breaks out right across the street from work, Babs is torn between her role as a superhero and dutiful Burrito Bucket employee. Will she be able to save the day and keep her job all in the nick of time?

description: When Wonder Woman is home for a holiday, Ares, the god of war, attacks.

title: Hero of the Month: Harley Quinn
description: Harley Quinn is anointed Hero of the Month.

description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

title: Hero of the Month: Wonder Woman
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M is Wonder Woman. Waller shows a video montage of Wonder Woman's exploits, which is mix of big heroic moments, and the small beats of friendship, laughter and fun. Wonder Woman's heroism isn't just about superpowers, but also about the amazing, caring person she is.

title: Hero of the Month: Poison Ivy
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Poison Ivy. Waller shows a video montage of Poison Ivy's exploits as Ivy saves the students from the grip of her out-of-control plants.

title: #SchoolGhoul
description: When Tatsu Yamashiro asks for help at a haunted all-girls academy, Barbara Gordon and Kara Danvers find themselves caught up in something much bigger than a ghost hunt.

title: Get to Know You: Barry Allen - Flash
description: Did you know the DC Super Hero Girls aren't the only super heroes at Metropolis High? Meet Barry Allen, the best dessert slinger at Sweet Justice. And incidentally, he's also The Flash, one of Batgirl's best friends.
